      <p class="font-heading font-bold text-charcoal-900 mb-2">Key Takeaway</p>
      <p class="text-charcoal-700 leading-relaxed">South Carolina provides strong consumer protections for preneed insurance purchases. Under SC Code &sect; 32-7, your preneed funds must be placed in trust or backed by insurance, and irrevocable preneed plans are exempt from Medicaid asset calculations &mdash; a critical planning tool for SC families.</p>
    </div>

    <!-- Author Byline -->
    <div class="bg-linen rounded-xl p-8 border border-border-light mb-8">
      <div class="flex items-start gap-4">
        <div class="w-16 h-16 rounded-full bg-teal-600/10 flex items-center justify-center flex-shrink-0">
